{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-219-Meet-Liquid-Glass","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-219-meet-liquid-glass"]}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Key-Takeaways","level":2,"text":"Key Takeaways"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"üåà Liquid Glass dynamically bends light and moves like gel"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"üß† Liquid Glass responds to the surrounding content"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"üß≠ Best used for the navigation layer"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"üé® Tint components to bring emphasis to primary elements","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"row","columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-219-WhatIsLiquidGlass","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":1},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-219-AdaptToSurroundingContent"}]}],"size":1}],"numberOfColumns":2},{"type":"row","columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-219-HowToUse"}]}]},{"size":1,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-219-Tinting","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"numberOfColumns":2},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Presenter","level":2,"text":"Presenter"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Chan Karunamuni, Apple Design Team","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Shubham Kedia, Apple Design Team","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Bruno Canales, Apple Design Team","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"What-is-Liquid-Glass","level":2,"text":"What is Liquid Glass"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-219-WhatIsLiquidGlass"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A new ‚Äúmaterial‚Äù that dynamically bends and shapes light and moves like a light weight liquid"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Designed to be rounded forms that float over content of an app"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previous materials focused on scattering light, while liquid glass bends light"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-219-LiquidGlassInteractivity"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On interactions, Liquid Glass will flex and energize with light","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Liquid Glass moves with gel-like flexibility in tandem with interactions","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Elements can temporarily lift up into Liquid Glass when interacting with a component."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Adaptivity","level":2,"text":"Adaptivity"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-219-AdaptToSurroundingContent","type":"image"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Liquid Glass components respond to the surrounding content"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As text scrolls underneath, shadows become more prominent to create separation"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Components can independently switch between light and dark mode","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Light from colorful content nearby can spill onto its surface"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-219-AdaptToSize","type":"image"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The size of a Liquid Glass components also effects the appearance"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Larger elements simulate a thicker more substantial material"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Shadows and scattering of light also increase with component size"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"How-to-use-Liquid-Glass","level":2,"text":"How to use Liquid Glass"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-219-HowToUse"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Best used for the navigation layer that floats above the content of an app","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Avoid stacking glass on glass","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When placing elements on top of Liquid Glass use fills and transparency for visual separation","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Variants","level":3,"text":"Variants"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-219-Variants"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"2 variants of Liquid Glass: Regular and Clear","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Do not mix the variants","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Regular","level":4,"text":"Regular"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"More versatile than clear and will be used more frequently"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Retains all adaptive behaviors previously discussed","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Clear","level":4,"text":"Clear"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Does not have adaptive behaviors"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Permanently more transparent to allow content underneath to come through"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Only use when the following conditions are met:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["  1. Elements are over media-rich content  ","  2. Content will not be negatively affected by a dimming layer","  3. Covered content is bold and bright"]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Tinting-Liquid-Glass","level":3,"text":"Tinting Liquid Glass"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-219-Tinting","type":"image"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Tinting allows you to apply color to Liquid Glass while staying consistent with the material","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tints should only be used to bring emphasis to primary elements"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Liquid Glass unifies Apple platform design language while providing a more dynamic and expressive user experience. Get to know the design principles of Liquid Glass, explore its core optical and physical properties, and learn where to use it and why."}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC25","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Meet Liquid Glass"},"sampleCodeDownload